# UI Rules

## Aesthetic Standards
- Premium, modern, uncluttered — this is a paid product, not a free tool
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes
- Animations via Framer Motion where appropriate
- Dark mode considered in all new UI

## Customer-Facing UI Rules
- No debug text, console output, or technical error messages in production UI
- No raw Stripe language ("invoice", "subscription_id", "customer portal")
- No RunPod job IDs or internal references visible to users
- No redundant buttons or duplicate actions
- Clear loading / error / success states on every interactive element
- Copy must be clear, human, and action-oriented

## Admin UI Rules
- Admin pages live entirely under `/admin/**`
- Admin nav components must not appear in customer shell
- Customer nav/components must not appear in admin shell
- Admin UI can use more technical language — it's operator-facing
- Admin pages should show real data — no placeholder or mock content

## Layout Architecture
- `components/SiteShell.tsx` — customer layout wrapper (nav + footer)
- `components/PrimaryNav.tsx` — customer top nav
- Admin has its own layout in `app/admin/layout.tsx`
- Never use `SiteShell` or `PrimaryNav` inside admin pages

## Component Rules
- Don't create a new component if an existing one can be extended
- Keep components in `/components/` if shared across 3+ pages
- Keep components co-located in their page folder if used in 1-2 places
- No tiny fragmented boxes unless they serve a clear information purpose

## State & Feedback
- Every form submission needs: loading state, success state, error state
- Use inline error messages (not alerts or console logs)
- Disable submit buttons while loading to prevent double-submit
- Show skeleton loaders or spinners for async data, not blank space

## Copy Guidelines
- "Your content" not "generated images"
- "Your account" not "subscription object"
- "Payment failed" not "invoice payment_failed"
- "Renews monthly" not "subscription active"
- "Something went wrong, please try again" for unexpected errors — never show stack traces
